1
00:00:12,390 --> 00:00:14,600
It starts off slow.

2
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:16,120
A single expression.

3
00:00:16,120 --> 00:00:17,920
Or just one move.

4
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:19,600
Once you accept the invite,

5
00:00:19,750 --> 00:00:21,230
the tango begins.

6
00:00:25,060 --> 00:00:25,540
Beautiful.

7
00:00:25,540 --> 00:00:26,220
Looks great.

8
00:00:26,220 --> 00:00:27,060
The flowers?

9
00:00:27,060 --> 00:00:28,380
You're stunning.

10
00:00:28,820 --> 00:00:29,900
Fasten it here, right?

11
00:00:30,060 --> 00:00:31,540
This is a dance of temptation.

12
00:00:32,220 --> 00:00:33,700
Also a dance of love.

13
00:00:34,660 --> 00:00:35,780
Do I feel super warm to you?

14
00:00:35,780 --> 00:00:37,660
Yeah, totally two extremes.

15
00:00:37,660 --> 00:00:38,500
I'm freezing.

16
00:00:41,180 --> 00:00:43,380
They say tango is a dance for two,

17
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:46,060
but in the depths of darkness,

18
00:00:46,820 --> 00:00:48,220
there's always a hidden third.

19
00:00:51,780 --> 00:00:52,540
You just got here?

20
00:00:52,860 --> 00:00:53,980
Having fun with your date?

21
00:00:53,980 --> 00:00:55,340
So, you two have made it official?

22
00:00:55,340 --> 00:00:57,660
Or will you try to get to know me?

23
00:00:57,860 --> 00:00:59,340
From the very beginning,

24
00:00:59,340 --> 00:00:59,980
my first choice

25
00:00:59,980 --> 00:01:00,760
has always been you.

26
00:01:03,700 --> 00:01:05,540
If you choose to dance with him,

27
00:01:05,540 --> 00:01:07,710
be ready to face the consequences.

28
00:01:08,760 --> 00:01:10,860
Passion can turn into jealousy.

29
00:01:12,020 --> 00:01:13,460
I need to talk to her for a moment.

30
00:01:13,940 --> 00:01:16,220
Love can make you act on impulse.

31
00:01:16,590 --> 00:01:19,300
Do you love me or (him)?

32
00:01:21,780 --> 00:01:24,980
Exactly. Tango exists to remind us

33
00:01:24,980 --> 00:01:26,260
that the greatest love

34
00:01:26,260 --> 00:01:27,860
will always stir the heart like waves.

35
00:01:28,980 --> 00:01:33,180
=Episode 3 (Part 1)
=The Tango of Love=

36
00:01:36,060 --> 00:01:39,780
(01:00 Xuan Cheng walks
Liu Jiayi back to her room)

37
00:01:39,780 --> 00:01:40,980
Let's go there.

38
00:01:42,630 --> 00:01:43,630
Go where?

39
00:01:47,530 --> 00:01:48,230
It's nice up here.

40
00:01:48,230 --> 00:01:49,270
Have you ever been up here?

41
00:01:49,270 --> 00:01:50,430
Never been there.

42
00:01:51,590 --> 00:01:52,590
Looks good up here.

43
00:01:54,870 --> 00:01:55,710
Can you walk?

44
00:01:55,710 --> 00:01:56,150
Yeah.

45
00:01:56,150 --> 00:01:57,463
Do you want me to hold your hand?

46
00:01:57,630 --> 00:01:58,310
Let's go.

47
00:02:01,030 --> 00:02:02,430
This place is really cozy.

48
00:02:02,430 --> 00:02:03,070
Yeah.

49
00:02:03,550 --> 00:02:04,550
Today,

50
00:02:04,870 --> 00:02:06,430
while you were out on that date,

51
00:02:07,390 --> 00:02:09,190
the rest of us who didn't join in

52
00:02:09,190 --> 00:02:10,670
were all hanging out

53
00:02:11,550 --> 00:02:12,990
at that restaurant.

54
00:02:13,043 --> 00:02:14,030
Everyone just sat around,

55
00:02:14,030 --> 00:02:15,390
chatting casually.

56
00:02:15,470 --> 00:02:17,270
I didn't feel like talking.

57
00:02:17,270 --> 00:02:18,390
Because my head was filled

58
00:02:18,390 --> 00:02:20,550
with what might happen to you

59
00:02:20,550 --> 00:02:21,750
during your date.

60
00:02:21,990 --> 00:02:23,630
I just couldn't focus.

61
00:02:23,630 --> 00:02:26,030
I walked over

62
00:02:26,030 --> 00:02:27,190
near the swing

63
00:02:27,630 --> 00:02:29,830
and stared out at the ocean.

64
00:02:39,190 --> 00:02:40,470
I watched the waves rolling in,

65
00:02:40,470 --> 00:02:41,550
and I thought

66
00:02:43,030 --> 00:02:45,030
that when you come back,

67
00:02:45,030 --> 00:02:46,030
I'll tell you how I feel.

68
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:46,630
Maybe...

69
00:02:48,190 --> 00:02:49,030
Anyway,

70
00:02:49,030 --> 00:02:50,990
I just want you to know

71
00:02:50,990 --> 00:02:51,830
that I...

72
00:02:56,830 --> 00:02:58,470
I really need you to know

73
00:02:58,470 --> 00:02:59,630
that I like you a lot.

74
00:03:01,903 --> 00:03:04,030
(19:30 Liu Jiayi back from the date)
A little secret.

75
00:03:04,030 --> 00:03:05,750
I'd regret it forever
if I didn't say it.

76
00:03:05,750 --> 00:03:06,990
I like you.

77
00:03:07,470 --> 00:03:08,110
That's right.

78
00:03:08,110 --> 00:03:09,125
(Straight-up confession)

79
00:03:09,136 --> 00:03:09,910
Unbelievable.

80
00:03:09,910 --> 00:03:10,350
Yes.

81
00:03:10,350 --> 00:03:11,670
I didn't hear that clearly.

82
00:03:11,830 --> 00:03:12,730
You didn't catch that?

83
00:03:13,910 --> 00:03:15,030
I said I like you.

84
00:03:15,750 --> 00:03:16,350
Yes.

85
00:03:19,276 --> 00:03:19,830
I don't think

86
00:03:19,830 --> 00:03:21,470
I treated it

87
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:23,270
as a serious confession.

88
00:03:23,270 --> 00:03:24,390
I just felt

89
00:03:25,550 --> 00:03:26,550
like I'd regret it

90
00:03:26,550 --> 00:03:27,830
if I hadn't told you.

91
00:03:27,830 --> 00:03:28,830
I meant it.

92
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:31,030
Sometimes,

93
00:03:31,470 --> 00:03:32,550
I'm not proactive.

94
00:03:32,550 --> 00:03:33,270
And also...

95
00:03:33,830 --> 00:03:35,470
Since I was a kid,

96
00:03:35,470 --> 00:03:37,910
I haven't been good

97
00:03:38,270 --> 00:03:40,750
at doing considerate things

98
00:03:41,550 --> 00:03:43,270
for girls.

99
00:03:44,270 --> 00:03:44,910
Honestly,

100
00:03:45,550 --> 00:03:46,190
it's just

101
00:03:47,830 --> 00:03:49,190
that I always feel

102
00:03:50,470 --> 00:03:51,670
like I'm one step behind.

103
00:03:53,390 --> 00:03:55,110
Honestly,

104
00:03:55,110 --> 00:03:55,830
I don't think

105
00:03:55,830 --> 00:03:57,390
dating

106
00:03:57,550 --> 00:03:58,190
is something

107
00:03:58,190 --> 00:03:59,910
we can control.

108
00:04:00,630 --> 00:04:01,470
Tomorrow,

109
00:04:01,470 --> 00:04:02,830
I'll win

110
00:04:02,830 --> 00:04:04,630
whatever it costs me.

111
00:04:04,630 --> 00:04:05,990
Just don't get hurt.

112
00:04:05,990 --> 00:04:07,550
I don't care if I get hurt.

113
00:04:07,830 --> 00:04:08,830
I must win.

114
00:04:08,896 --> 00:04:09,630
I really like you.

115
00:04:09,630 --> 00:04:10,270
Well.

116
00:04:10,830 --> 00:04:12,110
Just spend time alone with me,

117
00:04:12,463 --> 00:04:13,550
no matter what others think.

118
00:04:15,030 --> 00:04:16,790
You're pressuring me.

119
00:04:16,790 --> 00:04:17,830
I'm not pressuring you.

120
00:04:17,830 --> 00:04:18,950
I'm just kidding.

121
00:04:19,670 --> 00:04:21,456
Today made me feel

122
00:04:21,483 --> 00:04:22,190
that if this date

123
00:04:22,190 --> 00:04:24,550
turned out amazing,

124
00:04:24,550 --> 00:04:26,670
I might leave.

125
00:04:26,670 --> 00:04:28,070
It's hitting me deep.

126
00:04:35,830 --> 00:04:38,030
Anyway, I'm not letting you go.

127
00:04:45,230 --> 00:04:46,070
If they asked me

128
00:04:46,070 --> 00:04:47,390
to a mystery date today,

129
00:04:47,390 --> 00:04:48,470
I'd say I'm not going.

130
00:04:49,070 --> 00:04:50,070
I wouldn't go.

131
00:04:50,670 --> 00:04:51,950
I wouldn't go for sure.

132
00:04:51,950 --> 00:04:53,030
You'd definitely go.

133
00:04:53,270 --> 00:04:54,670
I wouldn't.

134
00:04:54,670 --> 00:04:56,350
I said I didn't want to go.

135
00:04:57,070 --> 00:04:57,470
First,

136
00:04:57,470 --> 00:04:58,950
I've only got so much energy.

137
00:04:58,950 --> 00:05:00,030
I was worn out.

138
00:05:00,656 --> 00:05:01,270
I can't do it.

139
00:05:01,270 --> 00:05:02,510
Mostly because you're tired.

140
00:05:02,510 --> 00:05:03,670
Way too tired.

141
00:05:04,030 --> 00:05:05,510
It's not mainly because of that.

142
00:05:05,790 --> 00:05:07,110
I was tired,

143
00:05:07,110 --> 00:05:08,270
but I didn't want to go.

144
00:05:09,630 --> 00:05:10,390
Pinky promise.

145
00:05:11,230 --> 00:05:13,230
Liars should be punished.

146
00:05:13,230 --> 00:05:14,270
Honestly, if it were me...

147
00:05:14,670 --> 00:05:17,030
Pinky promises for lies?

148
00:05:17,030 --> 00:05:19,070
Aren't they for making a deal?

149
00:05:19,670 --> 00:05:20,230
Really?

150
00:05:20,230 --> 00:05:21,270
Then if...

151
00:05:21,270 --> 00:05:22,030
Well.

152
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:23,270
I swear.

153
00:05:24,510 --> 00:05:25,230
Swear.

154
00:05:26,190 --> 00:05:26,790
I swear.

155
00:05:26,790 --> 00:05:27,830
I didn't want to go.

156
00:05:29,630 --> 00:05:31,670
I swear, too.

157
00:05:34,790 --> 00:05:35,950
I didn't want to go.

158
00:05:35,950 --> 00:05:37,790
You're the only one in my heart.

159
00:05:40,790 --> 00:05:42,390
I remember that moment.

160
00:05:42,390 --> 00:05:43,510
It was when you said

161
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:45,390
you didn't want to go.

162
00:05:45,390 --> 00:05:46,670
That actually made me happy.

163
00:05:47,830 --> 00:05:49,230
I don't want to go.

164
00:05:49,230 --> 00:05:53,820
(22:00, before the guys
dug out colorful shells)

165
00:06:02,550 --> 00:06:05,030
Today, my mood finally lifted.

166
00:06:05,510 --> 00:06:07,790
I'm looking forward to...

167
00:06:07,790 --> 00:06:08,790
Every single day.

168
00:06:23,620 --> 00:06:31,540
(Day-3)

169
00:06:51,950 --> 00:06:53,670
The wait feels so long.

170
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:56,670
On the island,

171
00:06:56,670 --> 00:06:58,110
the guys

172
00:06:58,110 --> 00:06:59,510
can't figure out

173
00:06:59,510 --> 00:07:00,510
if I have someone

174
00:07:00,510 --> 00:07:01,390
I'm curious about.

175
00:07:02,470 --> 00:07:04,950
There's been someone
that I've always wanted

176
00:07:04,950 --> 00:07:06,670
to know since Day 1.

177
00:07:48,950 --> 00:07:50,510
Have you been waiting here all along?

178
00:07:50,670 --> 00:07:52,670
Yeah, I've been waiting for you.

179
00:08:00,670 --> 00:08:02,510
Sorry for the long wait.

180
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:08,620
(My first choice from the start was)

181
00:08:08,620 --> 00:08:10,220
(Zhao Enda.)

182
00:08:10,230 --> 00:08:11,350
The most reassuring.

183
00:08:12,510 --> 00:08:13,070
Me?

184
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:14,830
(Day 1, ice-breaking)

185
00:08:14,830 --> 00:08:17,350
He gives off a steady vibe
at first glance,

186
00:08:17,350 --> 00:08:20,390
leaving me a good first impression.

187
00:08:20,390 --> 00:08:22,070
I think I can fall

188
00:08:22,070 --> 00:08:22,929
for someone instantly

189
00:08:22,940 --> 00:08:24,350
and be very proactive.

190
00:08:24,350 --> 00:08:26,790
I'm not shy about making the first move.

191
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:30,940
(Day 1, girls' affection delivery)

192
00:08:30,950 --> 00:08:32,710
Anyone you're liking so far?

193
00:08:33,110 --> 00:08:35,310
The reassuring one feels nice.

194
00:08:35,350 --> 00:08:36,230
Zhao Enda?

195
00:08:36,230 --> 00:08:36,790
Yeah.

196
00:08:37,110 --> 00:08:38,550
He looks cute.

197
00:08:39,110 --> 00:08:40,110
Do you cook?

198
00:08:40,310 --> 00:08:41,110
Nope.

199
00:08:41,110 --> 00:08:42,270
What did you make yesterday?

200
00:08:42,550 --> 00:08:43,670
Clay pot congee.

201
00:08:43,670 --> 00:08:44,550
So, you can cook.

202
00:08:44,550 --> 00:08:45,350
And pork ribs.

203
00:08:45,350 --> 00:08:46,670
The wacky pork ribs?

204
00:08:46,670 --> 00:08:47,910
Yeah, the wacky pork ribs.

205
00:08:52,870 --> 00:08:54,470
I'm curious about Zhao Enda.

206
00:08:54,481 --> 00:08:55,823
So, I tossed the ball over there.

207
00:08:56,260 --> 00:09:00,060
(Day 2, girls' affection delivery)

208
00:09:00,110 --> 00:09:03,230
Zhao Enda, please proceed

209
00:09:03,230 --> 00:09:05,470
to deliver your affection.

210
00:09:05,470 --> 00:09:07,470
I'm worried
he'll give all his votes to Yang.

211
00:09:07,470 --> 00:09:09,030
If he gives her all his votes,

212
00:09:09,030 --> 00:09:10,350
then I won't want

213
00:09:10,790 --> 00:09:11,790
to join in anymore.

214
00:09:11,790 --> 00:09:13,310
But you have no idea.

215
00:09:14,030 --> 00:09:15,470
I'll want to quit.

216
00:09:17,430 --> 00:09:19,790
I knew long ago

217
00:09:19,790 --> 00:09:20,310
that Yang

218
00:09:20,310 --> 00:09:21,550
likes him a lot.

219
00:09:21,550 --> 00:09:22,470
It's him.

220
00:09:23,430 --> 00:09:25,230
It's straightforward.

221
00:09:25,230 --> 00:09:26,276
The most attractive to you?

222
00:09:26,310 --> 00:09:26,910
Yeah.

223
00:09:30,670 --> 00:09:33,030
I need to think about how Yang feels.

224
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:34,470
How will she feel?

225
00:09:35,470 --> 00:09:36,470
Have you had breakfast?

226
00:09:36,470 --> 00:09:37,230
Yeah, I did.

227
00:09:37,590 --> 00:09:39,310
Your style is different from yesterday.

228
00:09:39,910 --> 00:09:40,910
Which one looks better?

229
00:09:41,710 --> 00:09:42,230
Today's.

230
00:09:42,230 --> 00:09:42,710
Thanks.

231
00:09:42,710 --> 00:09:43,743
I think today's is better.

232
00:09:44,670 --> 00:09:47,430
I didn't mean to look
like I'm competing.

233
00:09:47,430 --> 00:09:49,670
I'm worried
it might make people uncomfortable.

234
00:09:53,256 --> 00:09:54,590
Come down and join us at the beach

235
00:09:54,590 --> 00:09:55,470
for some Polaroids.

236
00:09:56,030 --> 00:09:58,790
We'll finish the hot pot first.

237
00:09:58,790 --> 00:09:59,230
Take it.

238
00:09:59,790 --> 00:10:00,910
Take it down.

239
00:10:03,030 --> 00:10:04,670
It kind of felt

240
00:10:04,670 --> 00:10:07,430
like I was stepping into their space.

241
00:10:07,590 --> 00:10:08,430
If I know

242
00:10:08,430 --> 00:10:10,263
they like each other,

243
00:10:10,274 --> 00:10:11,710
it'd be hard to push things further.

244
00:10:11,710 --> 00:10:12,952
But right now, there's nothing.

245
00:10:12,963 --> 00:10:14,110
Still, I think it's obvious.

246
00:10:14,470 --> 00:10:14,870
No way.

247
00:10:14,870 --> 00:10:16,156
You haven't even talked to him.

248
00:10:16,167 --> 00:10:17,399
You haven't said a word to him.

249
00:10:17,410 --> 00:10:18,110
How would you know

250
00:10:18,590 --> 00:10:19,710
if he likes you or not?

251
00:10:26,030 --> 00:10:27,470
I wanted to talk to you last night,

252
00:10:27,470 --> 00:10:28,550
but I didn't think

253
00:10:28,550 --> 00:10:30,670
it was the right moment.

254
00:10:32,230 --> 00:10:34,030
I didn't expect this.

255
00:10:36,350 --> 00:10:37,110
Well.

256
00:10:38,910 --> 00:10:41,470
Maybe you know what I'll say.

257
00:10:42,710 --> 00:10:44,230
You had no clue?

258
00:10:46,110 --> 00:10:47,670
I thought I made it pretty obvious.

259
00:10:51,030 --> 00:10:52,110
Go on.

260
00:10:52,110 --> 00:10:54,550
I didn't really get it.

261
00:10:54,710 --> 00:10:57,310
I was going to say this last night.

262
00:10:57,470 --> 00:10:58,990
But the timing

263
00:10:58,990 --> 00:11:00,310
was a bit off.

264
00:11:04,230 --> 00:11:05,230
Honestly,

265
00:11:07,470 --> 00:11:10,430
you've been my first choice
from the very start.

266
00:11:11,150 --> 00:11:12,030
Seriously?

267
00:11:20,550 --> 00:11:22,550
That's a real surprise to me.

268
00:11:22,550 --> 00:11:23,230
A huge surprise.

269
00:11:23,230 --> 00:11:24,225
I never saw that coming.

270
00:11:24,236 --> 00:11:25,030
Really?

271
00:11:25,230 --> 00:11:26,230
You got so many votes.

272
00:11:26,230 --> 00:11:27,430
Don't you know?

273
00:11:27,870 --> 00:11:29,430
I thought

274
00:11:30,910 --> 00:11:32,670
they were all from Yang.

275
00:11:32,670 --> 00:11:33,670
I never saw that coming.

276
00:11:33,790 --> 00:11:35,110
Definitely not.

277
00:11:36,590 --> 00:11:37,430
Really?

278
00:11:37,670 --> 00:11:38,870
I'm totally shocked.

279
00:11:38,870 --> 00:11:40,030
It kind of makes me feel...

280
00:11:40,230 --> 00:11:41,150
When everyone

281
00:11:41,150 --> 00:11:42,670
was sitting together,

282
00:11:42,670 --> 00:11:43,790
if I call you out alone,

283
00:11:43,790 --> 00:11:44,790
you might feel awkward

284
00:11:44,790 --> 00:11:47,590
or maybe uncomfortable.

285
00:11:47,590 --> 00:11:48,343
So, I haven't found

286
00:11:48,354 --> 00:11:50,030
the right moment

287
00:11:50,030 --> 00:11:51,310
to have a chat with you.

288
00:11:51,470 --> 00:11:52,790
And honestly,

289
00:11:52,790 --> 00:11:54,030
at the beginning,

290
00:11:54,030 --> 00:11:55,350
I thought you

291
00:11:55,350 --> 00:11:55,870
and...

292
00:11:55,870 --> 00:11:56,350
Yang?

293
00:11:56,350 --> 00:11:56,710
Yeah.

294
00:11:56,710 --> 00:11:58,230
I felt like you two had...

295
00:11:58,230 --> 00:11:59,030
You know.

296
00:11:59,470 --> 00:12:02,030
You spent a lot of time together.

297
00:12:02,030 --> 00:12:03,030
I kept worrying

298
00:12:03,030 --> 00:12:04,790
that Yang might not feel great

299
00:12:04,790 --> 00:12:05,670
about it,

300
00:12:05,670 --> 00:12:07,430
so I never found the right chance.

301
00:12:07,670 --> 00:12:07,910
Yeah.

302
00:12:07,910 --> 00:12:11,670
Because on the first day,

303
00:12:11,670 --> 00:12:12,870
we ended up sitting together.

304
00:12:12,870 --> 00:12:15,230
So, we talked quite a lot.

305
00:12:16,310 --> 00:12:17,430
So, are you two...

306
00:12:17,430 --> 00:12:17,790
Are you

307
00:12:17,790 --> 00:12:19,230
already sure about her,

308
00:12:19,230 --> 00:12:19,790
or

309
00:12:19,790 --> 00:12:22,310
still meeting other girls?

310
00:12:26,470 --> 00:12:27,790
Well, I think...

311
00:12:27,790 --> 00:12:30,230
I've only spent two days with Yang.

312
00:12:30,230 --> 00:12:31,670
Honestly, two days is too short

313
00:12:31,670 --> 00:12:33,910
for me to know her completely.

314
00:12:34,470 --> 00:12:36,230
So actually...

315
00:12:36,470 --> 00:12:37,399
You're still learning

316
00:12:37,410 --> 00:12:39,030
about other people.

317
00:12:39,870 --> 00:12:42,310
Maybe you can get to know me.

318
00:12:54,420 --> 00:12:55,420
(Yang, Zhan, Zhao)

319
00:12:55,430 --> 00:12:56,310
Honestly,

320
00:12:56,310 --> 00:12:58,030
during our private talk,

321
00:12:58,030 --> 00:13:01,110
a lot of boys like you.

322
00:13:02,670 --> 00:13:03,910
How about you?

323
00:13:07,230 --> 00:13:08,030
Me?

324
00:13:09,350 --> 00:13:10,670
I voted for you on the first day.

325
00:13:10,681 --> 00:13:12,069
(Day 1, boys' affection delivery)

326
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:14,900
(Zhao Enda > Zhan Jiaming: 1 weight)

327
00:13:14,900 --> 00:13:18,620
(Zhao Enda > Yang Tinghong: 2 weights)

328
00:13:18,910 --> 00:13:19,670
Really?

329
00:13:21,110 --> 00:13:22,230
But not on the second day.

330
00:13:23,230 --> 00:13:23,870
No.

331
00:13:27,030 --> 00:13:28,910
Do you think your choice
might change later?

332
00:13:32,110 --> 00:13:32,870
I'm not sure.

333
00:13:32,870 --> 00:13:34,470
Honestly, I really don't know.

334
00:13:34,470 --> 00:13:35,870
I'm still getting to know everyone.

335
00:13:35,870 --> 00:13:37,310
I warm up pretty slowly.

336
00:13:37,670 --> 00:13:38,670
Right now,

337
00:13:39,030 --> 00:13:42,110
I can't make up my mind
in just two days.

338
00:13:42,110 --> 00:13:43,110
It's just too quick.

339
00:13:45,940 --> 00:13:47,820
(Yang Tinghong, Zhan Jiaming, Zhao Enda)

340
00:13:50,670 --> 00:13:51,910
Let me put it another way.

341
00:13:51,910 --> 00:13:52,710
If I won

342
00:13:53,910 --> 00:13:55,310
today's game,

343
00:13:55,310 --> 00:13:56,110
I got a date

344
00:13:56,310 --> 00:13:57,563
with someone,

345
00:13:57,574 --> 00:13:58,670
and I invited you to dinner,

346
00:13:58,670 --> 00:14:01,670
would you find that awkward
or maybe not want to go?

347
00:14:04,030 --> 00:14:07,310
I might feel a bit of pressure.

348
00:14:07,310 --> 00:14:07,790
A little.

349
00:14:08,870 --> 00:14:09,990
Because...

350
00:14:26,870 --> 00:14:27,670
Hello.

351
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:31,260
(Yang Tinghong heads to the restaurant)

352
00:14:31,990 --> 00:14:33,910
Why are you two chatting here?

353
00:14:34,910 --> 00:14:37,150
Yeah, we were just talking.

354
00:14:39,470 --> 00:14:40,310
Sure, you guys chat.

355
00:14:41,310 --> 00:14:42,110
You two carry on.

356
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:45,100
(Village chief making rounds)

357
00:14:45,110 --> 00:14:46,910
Alright, let's finish this chat.

358
00:14:47,310 --> 00:14:48,110
Okay.

359
00:14:48,910 --> 00:14:49,470
Yeah.

360
00:14:49,470 --> 00:14:51,550
So, a couple of days ago,

361
00:14:51,550 --> 00:14:53,350
we didn't have much contact.

362
00:14:53,350 --> 00:14:54,310
There wasn't a chance.

363
00:14:54,310 --> 00:14:55,310
Because honestly,

364
00:14:55,403 --> 00:14:56,550
everything happened so fast.

365
00:14:56,550 --> 00:14:57,672
We didn't expect everyone

366
00:14:57,683 --> 00:14:58,910
to move ahead so quickly.

367
00:14:58,910 --> 00:14:59,110
I...

368
00:14:59,110 --> 00:14:59,910
Actually,

369
00:14:59,910 --> 00:15:01,670
if Yang hadn't reached out to me first,

370
00:15:01,670 --> 00:15:02,670
I'd take things slow too.

371
00:15:02,670 --> 00:15:04,470
I'm a naturally slow-paced person.

372
00:15:04,710 --> 00:15:06,110
I'm pretty passive

373
00:15:06,110 --> 00:15:07,550
by nature.

374
00:15:07,550 --> 00:15:09,470
So, when she came to chat with me,

375
00:15:09,710 --> 00:15:12,310
our conversations felt really nice.

376
00:15:12,310 --> 00:15:13,150
Very comfortable.

377
00:15:13,550 --> 00:15:15,430
My heart slowly opened up.

378
00:15:19,836 --> 00:15:21,230
You need some time to think, right?

379
00:15:21,230 --> 00:15:23,350
Yeah, I need to think it through.

380
00:15:26,030 --> 00:15:26,990
It's still pretty early.

381
00:15:27,230 --> 00:15:28,590
We're always the first ones here.

382
00:15:28,870 --> 00:15:29,350
Yeah.

383
00:15:37,310 --> 00:15:38,550
Two chefs.

384
00:15:40,470 --> 00:15:41,110
Morning.

385
00:15:41,210 --> 00:15:41,870
Morning.

386
00:15:41,870 --> 00:15:43,590
I just realized it's already noon.

387
00:15:43,590 --> 00:15:44,870
But we're still saying "morning".

388
00:15:45,110 --> 00:15:45,870
Yeah.

389
00:15:47,870 --> 00:15:48,670
No way.

390
00:15:48,670 --> 00:15:49,470
What's up?

391
00:15:49,470 --> 00:15:50,910
You're the one cooking today?

392
00:15:51,030 --> 00:15:53,230
Yep, and it's even for Xuan Cheng.

393
00:15:55,590 --> 00:15:57,470
That's impressive.

394
00:15:57,470 --> 00:15:58,670
Then I've gotta try it.

395
00:15:58,670 --> 00:15:59,470
It's burnt.

396
00:15:59,790 --> 00:16:01,030
That does happen with this one.

397
00:16:01,030 --> 00:16:01,736
It's fine.

398
00:16:01,747 --> 00:16:02,319
Take that off.

399
00:16:02,330 --> 00:16:03,550
It's fine.

400
00:16:03,550 --> 00:16:04,350
Can you eat that?

401
00:16:04,350 --> 00:16:04,590
No.

402
00:16:04,590 --> 00:16:05,350
I have to.

403
00:16:05,350 --> 00:16:06,030
You have to eat?

404
00:16:06,030 --> 00:16:06,550
I must eat.

405
00:16:06,550 --> 00:16:07,350
Okay.

406
00:16:08,550 --> 00:16:09,870
It's my pleasure.

407
00:16:13,230 --> 00:16:14,030
Hello.

408
00:16:14,230 --> 00:16:15,430
Morning.

409
00:16:16,110 --> 00:16:16,910
These sunglasses.

410
00:16:16,910 --> 00:16:18,550
You look so good.

411
00:16:18,550 --> 00:16:19,790
I think I'm falling for you.

412
00:16:19,790 --> 00:16:21,030
Not as good as you.

413
00:16:26,550 --> 00:16:27,230
Let me do it.

414
00:16:27,230 --> 00:16:28,230
It's alright.

415
00:16:28,230 --> 00:16:29,230
I've already done a lot.

416
00:16:29,230 --> 00:16:30,110
Let me finish it.

417
00:16:30,350 --> 00:16:31,710
It's rare for me to cook.

418
00:16:32,030 --> 00:16:33,030
My very first time.

419
00:16:33,470 --> 00:16:34,230
Okay.

420
00:16:35,550 --> 00:16:36,710
Cooking's not my strong suit.

421
00:16:37,030 --> 00:16:38,230
But...

422
00:16:38,230 --> 00:16:40,990
(Day 2 Evening, dating)
I could cook something for you.

423
00:16:40,990 --> 00:16:42,710
See if it tastes better than yours.

424
00:16:42,910 --> 00:16:43,230
Sure.

425
00:16:43,230 --> 00:16:44,350
I'll put my heart into it.

426
00:16:53,110 --> 00:16:54,110
Perfect.

427
00:16:55,970 --> 00:16:57,030
It's my first time cooking.

428
00:16:57,030 --> 00:16:57,870
Very perfect.

429
00:16:59,910 --> 00:17:01,230
Alright, my job here's done.

430
00:17:01,230 --> 00:17:02,310
It's your turn.

431
00:17:02,740 --> 00:17:04,500
(Sandwich)

432
00:17:27,190 --> 00:17:29,030
The village chief looks preoccupied.

433
00:17:29,030 --> 00:17:29,670
Yeah.

434
00:17:47,070 --> 00:17:48,950
You made breakfast with so much care.

435
00:17:48,950 --> 00:17:49,790
Why not eat it?

436
00:17:49,790 --> 00:17:51,030
You guys should have it.

437
00:17:51,910 --> 00:17:52,910
You two can share one.

438
00:17:54,830 --> 00:17:56,430
Actually, that sandwich was meant

439
00:17:56,430 --> 00:17:56,958
for Yan.

440
00:17:56,969 --> 00:17:58,830
I waited for a long time;
she never came back.

441
00:17:58,830 --> 00:17:59,936
So, we ended up sharing it.

442
00:18:04,950 --> 00:18:06,070
You can try just a little.

443
00:18:06,070 --> 00:18:07,070
I think it tastes good.

444
00:18:08,249 --> 00:18:09,830
I like having a sandwich in the morning.

445
00:18:10,853 --> 00:18:12,220
(Park Hyatt Sanya Sunny Bay Resort)

446
00:18:12,230 --> 00:18:13,310
This sun feels so nice.

447
00:18:13,310 --> 00:18:13,950
It really does.

448
00:18:15,230 --> 00:18:16,470
I can put them on now.

449
00:18:16,590 --> 00:18:17,350
Go ahead.

450
00:18:17,350 --> 00:18:18,710
I don't want your eyes to hurt.

451
00:18:20,683 --> 00:18:22,110
I'm curious if you can see me clearly

452
00:18:22,110 --> 00:18:23,590
with sunglasses on.

453
00:18:27,070 --> 00:18:27,830
Of course.

454
00:18:29,430 --> 00:18:30,070
What's up?

455
00:18:30,710 --> 00:18:31,550
Just curious.

456
00:18:31,550 --> 00:18:32,910
Because I can't see you well.

457
00:18:39,710 --> 00:18:40,830
Let's have some of this.

458
00:18:41,310 --> 00:18:42,190
Which one?

459
00:18:42,790 --> 00:18:43,190
This one.

460
00:18:45,190 --> 00:18:45,950
Do you want some?

461
00:18:46,350 --> 00:18:46,670
Yeah.

462
00:18:46,670 --> 00:18:48,430
I've been craving this.

463
00:18:54,950 --> 00:18:55,950
What fruit do you want?

464
00:18:56,230 --> 00:18:57,830
I love strawberries.

465
00:18:59,070 --> 00:18:59,430
Go ahead,

466
00:18:59,430 --> 00:19:00,670
since you like it.

467
00:19:00,950 --> 00:19:01,910
Thanks.

468
00:19:04,590 --> 00:19:06,910
Here, have a strawberry. I love them.

469
00:19:11,470 --> 00:19:12,110
Perfect.

470
00:19:12,110 --> 00:19:12,830
Alright.

471
00:19:17,830 --> 00:19:19,790
I've always wanted to visit Sanya.

472
00:19:20,070 --> 00:19:20,710
And...

473
00:19:20,876 --> 00:19:21,350
You're here.

474
00:19:21,350 --> 00:19:22,190
The view's amazing.

475
00:19:24,070 --> 00:19:25,710
We have to walk by the beach.

476
00:19:25,710 --> 00:19:26,830
Or you'll be leaving soon.

477
00:19:26,910 --> 00:19:28,190
We'll be heading out in a bit.

478
00:19:28,950 --> 00:19:30,190
True. Are you done?

479
00:19:31,430 --> 00:19:33,190
Then let's go.

480
00:19:40,190 --> 00:19:41,310
Absolutely gorgeous.

481
00:19:41,590 --> 00:19:42,190
Right?

482
00:19:42,190 --> 00:19:43,070
Yeah.

483
00:19:43,430 --> 00:19:44,710
We're both wearing white shoes.

484
00:19:44,943 --> 00:19:45,710
What a coincidence.

485
00:19:46,030 --> 00:19:46,710
True.

486
00:19:46,830 --> 00:19:48,030
Such a crazy coincidence.

487
00:19:48,596 --> 00:19:49,310
Can you handle it?

488
00:19:49,470 --> 00:19:50,830
I'll need your help.

489
00:19:53,836 --> 00:19:55,310
It looks so different in the daytime.

490
00:19:55,310 --> 00:19:56,190
Isn't it beautiful?

491
00:19:56,910 --> 00:19:57,710
Right?

492
00:19:57,910 --> 00:19:58,710
Yeah, really.

493
00:20:00,470 --> 00:20:01,470
So blue.

494
00:20:01,950 --> 00:20:03,590
The sand's so white.

495
00:20:03,590 --> 00:20:04,310
It's gorgeous.

496
00:20:08,509 --> 00:20:09,430
Do you need sunglasses?

497
00:20:09,430 --> 00:20:10,150
You can have them.

498
00:20:11,516 --> 00:20:12,590
Let me see your sunglasses.

499
00:20:13,350 --> 00:20:14,190
Put them on.

500
00:20:16,190 --> 00:20:17,470
They really block the sun.

501
00:20:18,710 --> 00:20:19,790
It suits you pretty well.

502
00:20:19,830 --> 00:20:20,190
Oh, yeah?

503
00:20:26,470 --> 00:20:27,190
Careful.

504
00:20:28,710 --> 00:20:30,470
Do you need my help?

505
00:20:30,470 --> 00:20:31,310
Sure.

506
00:20:36,910 --> 00:20:37,710
Someone's playing.

507
00:20:37,710 --> 00:20:38,470
Did you see it?

508
00:20:39,710 --> 00:20:40,810
I can barely see anything.

509
00:20:41,870 --> 00:20:42,950
Let me put them on for you.

510
00:20:55,910 --> 00:20:57,190
Do you like hiking?

511
00:20:57,230 --> 00:20:58,430
Yeah.

512
00:20:58,430 --> 00:20:59,070
Seriously?

513
00:20:59,070 --> 00:20:59,590
Yeah.

514
00:20:59,590 --> 00:21:00,670
When I was in Australia,

515
00:21:00,670 --> 00:21:02,470
I used to go see the sunrise
in the mornings.

516
00:21:07,430 --> 00:21:08,430
We can watch the sunrise

517
00:21:08,430 --> 00:21:09,830
on the island.

518
00:21:10,230 --> 00:21:11,110
Sounds good.

519
00:21:14,776 --> 00:21:15,710
We'll head back later.

520
00:21:16,030 --> 00:21:17,190
I'm very introverted.

521
00:21:17,230 --> 00:21:18,430
You're introverted, right?

522
00:21:19,483 --> 00:21:20,523
I've said so much to you.

523
00:21:20,534 --> 00:21:21,923
And you still think I'm introverted?

524
00:21:21,934 --> 00:21:22,830
I'm pretty outgoing.

525
00:21:23,030 --> 00:21:23,710
Seriously?

526
00:21:23,710 --> 00:21:24,550
But I stay silent

527
00:21:24,550 --> 00:21:26,070
with people I don't feel

528
00:21:26,070 --> 00:21:26,910
like talking to.

529
00:21:30,910 --> 00:21:31,590
Come on.

530
00:21:31,590 --> 00:21:32,190
Let's chat.

531
00:21:32,769 --> 00:21:33,590
You wanna talk here?

532
00:21:33,590 --> 00:21:34,710
Or should we go outside?

533
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:35,810
We can talk while we walk.

534
00:21:35,830 --> 00:21:36,670
Sure.

535
00:21:38,070 --> 00:21:38,950
Hello.

536
00:21:38,950 --> 00:21:40,230
Morning.

537
00:21:40,230 --> 00:21:41,430
Are you a zebra?

538
00:21:41,590 --> 00:21:42,950
Yep, I'm a zebra today.

539
00:21:45,070 --> 00:21:45,590
So,

540
00:21:45,590 --> 00:21:47,190
what do you want to say?

541
00:21:48,070 --> 00:21:48,730
I was thinking

542
00:21:48,741 --> 00:21:50,430
that if we're teaming up
for a game today,

543
00:21:50,430 --> 00:21:51,830
I want to bring you along.

544
00:21:52,710 --> 00:21:54,670
I was wondering
if we could work together.

545
00:21:55,070 --> 00:21:56,030
Work together how?

546
00:21:56,030 --> 00:21:57,310
Well, I noticed just now

547
00:21:57,310 --> 00:21:58,830
that Enda was talking to you.

548
00:21:58,830 --> 00:21:59,190
Yeah.

549
00:21:59,190 --> 00:22:01,110
I never found the right moment

550
00:22:01,110 --> 00:22:02,310
to chat or anything.

551
00:22:02,430 --> 00:22:03,670
Do you want a date today?

552
00:22:04,056 --> 00:22:05,070
Honestly, I'd like to have

553
00:22:05,070 --> 00:22:07,110
a real, official chance

554
00:22:07,110 --> 00:22:08,143
to get to know each other.

555
00:22:08,230 --> 00:22:09,670
Actually,

556
00:22:09,670 --> 00:22:10,430
what I worry about

557
00:22:10,430 --> 00:22:12,470
is that it feels

558
00:22:13,310 --> 00:22:14,310
like I shouldn't step in.

559
00:22:14,430 --> 00:22:15,190
No, not at all.

560
00:22:15,190 --> 00:22:16,836
Yeah, I just feel that way.

561
00:22:16,847 --> 00:22:17,583
We've come here.

562
00:22:17,650 --> 00:22:19,416
No matter how it turns out,

563
00:22:19,427 --> 00:22:20,605
the only thing that matters

564
00:22:20,616 --> 00:22:21,419
is being yourself.

565
00:22:21,430 --> 00:22:23,070
I'll slowly learn to open up.

566
00:22:23,070 --> 00:22:23,590
Actually...

567
00:22:23,590 --> 00:22:23,950
Well.

568
00:22:23,950 --> 00:22:24,930
I just wanted to say

569
00:22:24,930 --> 00:22:26,039
that when the game starts,

570
00:22:26,050 --> 00:22:26,810
we can be partners.

571
00:22:26,810 --> 00:22:27,690
(Teammates in advance)

572
00:22:27,690 --> 00:22:28,230
After we win,

573
00:22:28,230 --> 00:22:29,670
we can ask out whoever we want to.

574
00:22:29,670 --> 00:22:30,430
I'll help you win.

575
00:22:30,430 --> 00:22:31,190
Thank you.

576
00:22:35,603 --> 00:22:36,123
Well.

577
00:22:36,134 --> 00:22:37,083
I just wanted to ask you

578
00:22:37,094 --> 00:22:38,085
if you have other girls

579
00:22:38,096 --> 00:22:39,710
you'd like to get to know better.

580
00:22:44,430 --> 00:22:45,950
I was thinking about this yesterday.

581
00:22:48,190 --> 00:22:49,710
At first, I thought

582
00:22:50,430 --> 00:22:52,670
I should make a firm choice
about someone.

583
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:53,660
(Glances)

584
00:22:54,070 --> 00:22:54,670
Then I

585
00:22:54,670 --> 00:22:56,670
wouldn't get close to other girls.

586
00:22:57,910 --> 00:23:00,430
But being so sure about someone

587
00:23:00,430 --> 00:23:01,950
on the first day

588
00:23:01,950 --> 00:23:04,070
might not be a good thing.

589
00:23:05,830 --> 00:23:06,790
I think

590
00:23:06,790 --> 00:23:09,070
you should get to know everyone

591
00:23:09,070 --> 00:23:11,310
and pick the best person

592
00:23:11,310 --> 00:23:12,190
for you.

593
